bilingual.source: Once a lumbering center, it now has varied industries.
bilingual.target: 曾是一个伐木业中心, 如今具有各种各样的工业.

bilingual.source: Float it on the wanton wind and spread it in varied wonders.
bilingual.target: 使它飘浮在那肆无忌惮的风里，铺设成为各种各样的奇迹。

bilingual.source: This product should not be uesd as a substitute for a varied diet.
bilingual.target: 本产品不应使用代替了各种各样的饮食.

bilingual.source: All day a stream of pennies, varied by silver, poured in upon me, and it was a very bad day in which I failed to take 2 pounds.
bilingual.target: 整天都有各种各样的银币流水般地进入我的囊中，如果哪天收入不到两英镑，那就算是运气不济的了。

bilingual.source: And cancer charities believe that tomatoes and tomato-based products should play a prominent part in a varied and healthy diet.
bilingual.target: 癌症慈善团体组织认为西红柿和其制品在各种各样的健康绿色食品中的作用十分显著。

bilingual.source: Sure, from time to time you are explicitly assigned varied guidelines and instructions, but the majority of your decisions are yours alone to make.
bilingual.target: 没错，你偶尔会被很明确地分配各种各样的指导方针和操作说明，但是你大多数的决定都是你自己做出来的。

bilingual.source: The evolutionary basis of monotony is probably to prompt the animal to seek a varied diet to guard against the nutritional inadequacy of any one food item.
bilingual.target: 厌旧的进化基础可能是促使动物寻找各种各样的食物，以应对单一食物的营养缺失。

bilingual.source: In cooperation with nationality clubs, student associations and other organizations, the International Center provides a varied program of cultural and social events throughout the year.
bilingual.target: 国际中心还与国籍俱乐部，学生社团和其它组织合作，提供全年的各种各样的文化和社交活动。
使用了多样的句子开头。

bilingual.source: The colors of neon lamp can be varied.
bilingual.target: 霓虹灯的颜色可以是多种多样的。

list.abstract: varied，英语单词，主要用作形容词、动词，作形容词时译为“各式各样的；多变的；杂色的”，作动词时译为“变化，改变；使多样化（vary 的过去式和过去分词）”。

yingyinNormal.en: It's no fault of Quiznos. They have a varied menu.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这不是店家的错，他们的菜单很丰盛。

yingyinNormal.en: China's vast and varied land has helped shape a nation and its people.
yingyinNormal.zh: 中国得广袤土地囊括万象，孕育了这个国家，养育了它的人民。

yingyinNormal.en: Less varied? Not at all. We dine with four and 20 families of all shapes and sizes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 碰不到？完全不是。就我所知，平常跟我们来往吃饭的可也有二十四家呀，各色各样的家庭。

yingyinNormal.en: I find it perfectly adequate. Even if society is a little less varied than in town.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我觉得非常的适当，乡下碰不到像城里那么多些各色各样的人。

yingyinNormal.en: So varied is the food here that people fondly joke that Cantonese will eat anything with four legs that isn't a table!
yingyinNormal.zh: 这里的食物无比繁多，人们爱开玩笑说，广东人，四条腿的东西，除了桌子啥都吃。

yingyinNormal.en: Chinese food is as rich and varied as any on earth with thousands of dishes to choose from, all cooked in a variety of ways using a host of ingredients grown right across the vast nation.
yingyinNormal.zh: 中国食物丰富和多样举世无双，有成千上万种菜肴可供选择，都以不同的方法烹饪，使用的是中国本土生长的食材。

yingyinNormal.en: Centuries of living in different conditions, eating different food and encountering different neighbors turned similar dialects with varied pronunciation and vocabulary into radically different languages, continuing to divide as populations grew and spread out further.
yingyinNormal.zh: 几个世纪的不同生活条件，不同食物，不同邻居，使原本相似而只是发音和词汇有所不同的方言变成了完全不同的语言，并随着人口的增长和迁移不断分化。
